Kirchhoff Plans $20.5 Million Plant in Romania, Mediafax Reports

-- B y   I r i n a   S a v u
-- 
2011-09-28T11:53:11Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-28/kirchhoff-plans-20-5-million-plant-in-romania-mediafax-reports.html
German car-parts maker Kirchhoff
Automotive GmbH will invest 15 million euros ($20.5 million) in
a plant in southern  Romania ,  Mediafax  reported, citing Chief
Executive Officer Arndt Kirchhoff.  The plant will start production next year and will supply
parts to  Ford Motor Co. (F) ’s Romanian unit, Fiat SpA’s Serbian
facility and  Renault SA (RNO) , the Bucharest-based news service said,
citing Kirchhoff.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Irina Savu in Bucharest at 
 isavu@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  